node.text:
-
SAVE & SHARE this little message 👇🏼
-
Confession, I don’t care for feeling like a newbie at anything, especially when it comes to physical challenges. But what I dislike even more is getting comfortable and staying within that comfort zone. I consciously place myself in challenging situations so that I can grow not only physically, but most importantly, mentally, past self limiting perceptions. Though it might not come easy, when you feed your mind with messages like “I CAN” and with the actions you do, the mind rewards you with more confidence, will and ability to act even when it fears change. So, my advice, challenge yourself constantly. Don’t conform and don’t stay within your comfort zone. There’s so much growth past it. 🙌🏼
-
The wheelbarrow was the toughest thing I’ve done in a long time. Pushing here up the hill a total of 130 lbs 💀
-
Thank you once more @pit_master @heather.hackleman @thepitmartialarts @antoniobanuelos and everyone at The Pit in San Luis Obispo accommodating a total newbie 🙏🏻💚
-
#fitness #fitnessmotivation #motivation #challenge #workoutmotivation #mma

node.text:
LIKE + SAVE + SHARE 💚
-
Mindful Saturday’s - today I thought of bringing you one of my favorite breathing techniques that actually helps tighten your abdominal muscles and helps with digestion. Do this before you eat, early in the morning. The meditation part you can do anytime. So helpful during these stressful times in easing anxiety and calming the mind. 🙌🏼 You may chose to sit like me or on a chair, back straight, and feet in contact with the ground.
-
Breathing:
Contraindications and Cautions (do not perform if you have the following and caution with any other similar ailments)
-Stomach or intestinal ulcers
-Hernia
-High blood pressure
-Heart disease
-Glaucoma
-Menstruation
-Pregnancy
Technique:
1. Breathe deeply through the nose
2. Exhale through your nose or pursed lips all the air out of your lungs
3. Perform a “mock inhalation" - expand your rib cage as if you were inhaling, but don't actually inhale. Bring your abdominals in towards your spine and upward creating a diaphragmatic vacuum.
4. Release abdominal muscles and breathe through your nose.
Repeat at least 3 times up to 10 times
——
Meditation (went a bit longer 😅):
You may stay longer with any body part and extend the meditation. Obviously the longer the meditation session the more the benefits you may reap. But even a quick session is way better than nothing. Great to perform at least once a day and as many times as you’d like should you need to center or if you’re experiencing stress and anxiety
-
Hope you enjoy it 💚
-
-
-

SAVE + LIKE + SHARE ✅ & Comment what tutorial you would like to see next😊
-
Bulgarian Split Squat Benefits:
• Better range of motion
• Overload the quads and glutes
• Recruit stabilizer muscles
• Reduce muscle imbalances
• Allow for variety in weights and locations: barbell, DBs, KBs, etc
-
Main muscles worked:
Quads & Glutes 🍑
-
Form:
• Start w an appropriate height for your back leg so that you are able to go up and down in an almost vertical motion
• The shin on your front leg is perpendicular to the ground, knee slightly forward
• Hips are squared and back is neutral
• Lower vertically down till your back knee almost touches the ground
• When lowering down, your front knee follows the direction of your toes
• Lift back up to the starting position by pushing through the heel of your front foot
• Most of your weight and push comes from your front foot (about 90%)
-

Here we go again. Another tutorial for you loves, so make sure to:
SAVE + LIKE + SHARE ♥️ to keep em coming 🙌🏼
-
RDL main muscles worked:
1. Hamstrings
2. Glutes
3. Lower back
Other muscles worked: calves, adductors, mid and upper back, lats, traps, forearms...
-
RDL key points to keep in mind that can be utilized with not just a smith machine, but DBs, KBs, Olympic bar, etc:
1. Hinge at the hips, aka, bend at the hips - do not bend over at the spine, but rather bring hips back as far as possible
2. Soft, slightly bent knees, about 15% bent. Do not lock your knees
3. Maintain strong, neutral spine throughout the movement. Think of a rigid back
4. Keep chest out, shoulders rolled back and down, and CORE tight
5. As in a squat, push the knees out, placing more load on the outer edges of your feet, while pressing the big toes down into the floor
6. Keep weight close to center mass of body by lowering and lifting it alongside the front of your body (although one can have dumbbells along the outside of the legs, as long as they are kept at center mass)
7. Flex lats throughout movement (pushing chest out will help here)
8. Go to about mid shin level, where you feel a pull at the hamstrings, but you’re still maintaining a strong, neutral/straight back. Do not compromise the back by going further than your torso being parallel to the floor
9. Come back up to starting position by driving hips forward, squeezing the glutes and standing tall, again by unhinging at the hips and keeping at all times a strong straight back
-
Hope this helps friends 💗
-
Wearing  @ryderwear Botanics set in XS. 💎 Link in bio. Use code SG10 for discount. 🥰
-
REMEMBER: Mind-muscle connection. Squeeze, feel, touch, think about the working muscle. 🧠+💪🏼
-
Enjoy 😊
-
-

node.text:
Six Pack Abs Sunday 🍫 Tree optional

Train with ME on my NEW Crush It by Senada Greca App 👉🏼 ALL Levels, HOME or GYM, Meal plans and so much more 🔗🔗 in My BIO 💚
-
SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT
-
Hope you are all having an AMAZING Sunday 🙏🏻 If you find yourself in nature, with a strong tree like this, crush this quick ab workout! You’ll feel so connected 🙌🏼.
And don’t worry. I LOVE nature more than anything and this tree is one of the strongest trees out there.
Workout deets: 10-16 reps, hold for 30 secs on the L sit, 3-4 rounds
-
-
Remember, mind-muscle connection 🧠 +💪🏼. It’s not how much you lift, but HOW you lift 😉
-
Have Fun ☺️
-
-
-
-

node.text:
CrusHIIT Full Body 🤩 Tell me about your favorite vacation spot 🏝
-
Sipping on @womensbest BCAAs (brand partner)
-
SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT 👊🏼 w My Crush It Crew 🔗 in BIO 💚 to access ALL my Programs and Meal Plans and MORE 🤯
-
Happy Friday friends!!! If you need a good sweat session 💦 this workout is it. It’s similar to my CrusHIIT workout series (link in my BIO)! My HIIT style workouts (DON’T WORRY 😉 There’s 3 difficulty levels 😬)!!! 38 minutes long with rest time... bodyweight only... 🙌🏼
-
I personally would love a few days off 😅. It’s been so busy with upcoming projects, so right about now, swimming in the ocean and chilling under an umbrella with a cold drink, somewhere tropical, sounds dreamy. Soon, soon hopefully 🙏🏻 
-
Workout deets: 45 secs ON 15 secs OFF (beginners modify as necessary and start with 15-30 secs then rest for 45-30 secs): 3-4 rounds

node.text:
Full Body ANYWHERE 🔥

Did you know the EXPERT program in my Crush It by Senada Greca App (link in BIO to enroll first) is entirely doable with bands and light Dumbbells??? 🤯🤯🤯

SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT ANYWHERE 💪🏼

No, I’m not currently on vacation in Turks and Caicos (wish I was 😅), where this was filmed, I just had forgotten to share. So here it is: 12-16 reps, 3-4 sets
1. Reverse flies w squat jump
2. Push up to alt knee tucks
3. Switch jump lunge w rows
4. Sliding lateral lunges w curls
5. RDL to squat w front raise
6. Narrow stance squat w vida even pull variation
7. Alt leg curtsy lunge w tri extension
8. Static V w flies & knee tuck
-
👉🏼START your FIT LIFE TODAY! Train with ME in my new CRUSH IT by Senada Greca App
All the programs, Beginner to Expert, you’ve come to love, plus BRAND NEW Programs and Bonus features, including yoga 🙌🏼
Meal plans included and personalized to your macros
Brand NEW CONTENT and RECIPES added throughout your journey 💚
-
Remember, mind-muscle connection 🧠 +💪🏼. It’s not how much you lift, but HOW you lift 😉
-
Have Fun ☺️
-
-
-

node.text:
Be Blind to Haters! And the LOUDEST perpetrator, can be the little voice in you that tells you to stop... that you need a break... that this is too much... that you can’t do it... that you’re not good enough... that you will never change... why even bother...

Push past naysayers and limiting thoughts. Even if the naysayer is you. Even if the limiting thoughts are yours. You can achieve more than most or you, give yourself credit for. Read that again! And again! 💚

My marathoning days might be behind me, but when I was told I couldn’t and shouldn’t run a 10k, I decided to run 3 marathons and beat my time at each one! And if I can, you dang well CAN TOO! YOU can do anything, YOU decide you can!

#running #cardioworkout #getfit #fitnessmotivation #motivation

EPIC Glute / Leg Day 🔥🔥🔥
-
SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT with my Crew 🔗🔗 in my BIO 💚
-
Happy Monday beautiful souls! I hope you had a great weekend and I wish you an even more amazing week ahead! Keep crushing it 💪🏼
-
We crush a Glute & Leg workout on a Monday to start the week off on a powerful note 💪🏼
-
Workout: 10-14 reps for 3-4 sets each:
1. Plate swing w squat combo
2. Sissy squats
3. Sumo straddle squat
4. Lateral lunge to sumo
5. Single leg RDL
6. Good morning to alt leg lunge back
7. Curtsy step up
8. Weighted single leg hammie curl ins
9. Single leg hip thrust
-
TRAIN with ME! For access to all my programs, HIIT workouts, meal plans, private group tap 🔗🔗 in my BIO 💚
-
Remember, mind-muscle connection 🧠 +💪🏼. It’s not how much you lift, but HOW you lift 😉
-
-
-
-

node.text:
Six Pack Abs Sunday 🍫

Train with me 🔗🔗 in My BIO 💚 (details below)

SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT 👊🏼 w My Crew
-
It’s sunny, it’s Sunday... it’s Six Pack Abs Sunday 🙌🏼 What are you up to today???
-
Today I went for a quick run, which felt amazing and did some ab work. I don’t run often anymore, but when I do, I love it.
-
Workout deets 12-16 reps for 3-4 sets:
1. Supine oblique reverse crunches
2. Hollow body leg hold w crunches
3. Hollow body scissors kicks
4. Table top to hollow body
5. Crunches w alt knee tucks
-
👉🏼START your FIT LIFE TODAY with my brand NEW CRUSH IT by Senada Greca App. LINK in my BIO to enroll first 🙌🏼
All the programs you’ve come to love, plus BRAND NEW Programs and Bonus features, including yoga 🙌🏼
Meal plans included and personalized to your macros
Brand NEW CONTENT and RECIPES added throughout your journey 💚
-
Remember, mind-muscle connection 🧠 +💪🏼. It’s not how much you lift, but HOW you lift 😉
-
Have Fun ☺️
-
-
-

WANT: To “Cinch” Yo Waist? Stronger Core? Engaged Deep Abdominals? Etc etc?

If your belly is protruding and you can’t do this, your deep core muscles are WEAK 😩

DO: DIAPHRAGMATIC HOLDS to strengthen them!

Obviously diet is a huge part for a “flat” tummy, and this alone won’t give you a six pack, but in order to truly engage your deep ab muscles that hold your belly in, diaphragmatic holds are golden 🏅

3-5 rounds to start then increase. Hold for as long as you can, but watch out for dizziness ⚠️ so perform seated as a beginner

#abs #coreworkout #flattummy #sixpack
